00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,120
has always been of
the greatest repugnance to me.

254
00:11:57,160 --> 00:12:01,200
Although, far be it from me
to impugn the nature of
your trade or profession.

255
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:03,760
Do go on.

256
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,120
Well, we've always been good
friends, sharing interests.

257
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:09,200
Gardening, model airplanes,
the sixpenny bottle
for the holiday money.

258
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:12,320
And twice a month,
settling down at night to
do the accounts.

259
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:13,960
Something which,
uh, Deirdre,

260
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,000
Deirdre, that's my wife, uh,

261
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:18,320
particularly looked forward to
on account of her feet.

262
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:20,160
I should probably
have said at the outset

263
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,080
that I'm noted for having
a sense of humor,

264
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,520
although I've kept to myself
over the last two years,

265
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,520
notwithstanding as it were,
and it's only
comparatively recently

266
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:29,320
that I have begun
to realize, well--

267
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:31,680
Uh, perhaps "realize"
is not the correct word.

268
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,240
Uh, imagined.

269
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:39,000
Imagine that I was not
the only thing in her life.

270
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,560
You suspected
your wife?

271
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:44,240
Well, yes. Yes.

272
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:47,000
At first, frankly, yes.

273
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:49,640
Her behavior did seem
at the time to me,

274
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:52,600
who was after all,
there to see,
to be a little odd.

275
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:55,600
-Odd?
-Yes. Well, I mean, uh,
to a certain extent, yes.

276
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,960
I'm not by nature
a suspicious person.
Far from it.

277
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:01,680
I have a reputation as
an after-dinner speaker,
if you take my meaning.

278
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,320
-Yes, I certainly do.
-Yeah.

279
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,000
Anyway, in the area
where I'm known,

280
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:06,760
the people, in fact,
know me extremely well.

281
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:09,160
-Right.
-Heh.

282
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,640
Would you hold this?
Thank you.

283
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:12,680
Yes. Anyway,
as I said,

284
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:15,680
I must learn to
face up to the facts,
stop beating about the bush,

285
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:18,560
or I'd never look myself
in the bathroom mirror again.

286
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,840
Anyway. So--

287
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,440
Would you mind running along
for 10 minutes?

288
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,720
-No.
-Make it half an hour.

289
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,280
Right. Oh, fine.

290
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:28,000
Yes. I'll wait outside,
shall I?

291
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,560
Yes, well, that's perhaps
the best thing. Yes.

292
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:34,360
Certainly put
my mind at rest on--

293
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:37,360
on one or two points there.

294
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:44,040
Now, wait there,
stranger.

295
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:50,680
A man can run and run
for year after year...

296
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:54,520
until he realizes that what
he's running from is hisself.

297
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:56,320
Gosh.

298
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:58,560
Now, a man's gotta do
what a man's gotta do,

299
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:01,040
and there ain't
no sense in runnin'.

300
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:04,680
Now, you gotta turn,
and you gotta fight.

301
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:06,640
And you gotta hold
your head up high.

302
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,160
Yes.

303
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:11,360
Now, you go back in there,
my son, and be a man.

304
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,960
Walk tall.

305
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,160
Yes.

306
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:17,280
Oh, I will.

307
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,000
I will.

308
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:21,400
I've been pushed around
long enough.

309
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,360
This is it!

310
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,200
This is your moment,
Arthur Pewtey.

311
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,440
This is it, Arthur Pewtey.

312
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:31,400
At last... you're a man!

313
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,320
[DEIRDRE GIGGLING]

314
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,160
All right, Deirdre,
come out of there!

315
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,920
-COUNSELOR: Go away.
-Right, right.

316
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,320
DEIRDRE:
Oh. Oh. Oh.

317
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,480
[GIGGLES]

318
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:52,240
ANNOUNCER:
<i>So much for pathos.</i>

319
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:03,840
NARRATOR:
<i>These historic pictures</i>
<i>of Queen Victoria,</i>

320
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:06,720
<i>taken in 1880 at Osborne,</i>

321
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,560
